物.definition: (bound form) thing; (literary) the outside world as distinct from oneself; people other than oneself

物事.definition: (literary) affair; matter; business; (dialect) item; thing; stuff

物以稀為貴.definition: the rarer sth is, the greater its value (idiom)

物以類聚.definition: similar things come together (idiom); like draws like; Birds of a feather flock together.

物以類聚，人以群分.pinyin: wù yǐ lèi jù ， rén yǐ qún fēn
物以類聚，人以群分.definition: Similar things group together, similar people fit together (idiom); Birds of a feather flock together.

物候.definition: natural phenomena of a seasonal nature

物候學.definition: the study of seasonal phenomena (flouring, migration etc)

物力.definition: physical resources (as opposed to labor resources)

物是人非.definition: things have remained the same, but people have changed

物業.definition: property; real estate; abbr. for 物業管理|物业管理[wu4 ye4 guan3 li3], property management

物極必反.definition: when things reach an extreme, they can only move in the opposite direction (idiom)

物欲.definition: material desire; craving for material things

物歸原主.definition: (idiom) to return sth to its rightful owner

物盡其用.definition: to use sth to the full; to make the best use of everything

物種起源.definition: Charles Darwin's "On the Origin of Species"

物管.definition: property management (abbr. for 物業管理|物业管理[wu4 ye4 guan3 li3])

物美價廉.definition: good quality and cheap; a bargain

物色.definition: to look for; to seek out; to choose

物質.definition: matter; substance; material; materialistic; CL:個|个[ge4]

物質文明和精神文明.pinyin: wù zhì wén míng hé jīng shén wén míng
物質文明和精神文明.definition: material and spiritual culture; matter and mind; material progress, ideology and culture (philosophic slogan, adopted into Deng Xiaoping theory from 1978)

物超所值.definition: (of a product, service etc) worth more than the cost; great value for the money spent
